article.headline: Pierce helps Princeton beat Cornell 79-77 for eight straight victory
article.description: — Caden Pierce scored 23 points to help Princeton extend its win streak to eight with a 79-77 victory over Cornell on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Pierce helps Princeton beat Cornell 79-77 for eight straight victory

video.title: Princeton Powers Past Cornell  - Via Ivy League
video.description: Caden Pierce Scores 23 to lead Princeton Past Cornell

article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- — Caden Pierce scored 23 points to help Princeton extend its win streak to eight with a 79-77 victory over Cornell on Saturday night. Pierce added eight rebounds and three steals for the Tigers (23-3, 11-2 Ivy League). Matt Allocco made three 3-pointers and scored 19. Xaivian Lee had 16 points. Nazir Williams led the Big Red (21-6, 10-3) with 23 points, six rebounds and five assists. Chris Manon added 17 points, six rebounds and two blocks. Guy Ragland Jr. scored nine. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
